						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Assuming that I have a soundtrack, i.e. it is known what notes are put into what APU channel for what amount of time: How complex is the actual code for this?</div><br /><br />The code for my music player is about 1000 lines of assembly, and took me about a week to write.<br /><br />Famitone2 is about 1500 lines. I don't know how long Shiru spent on it.<br /><br />If you've never worked with the APU before, expect to spend a lot of time figuring things out. If you just want to get it working, you might as well use Famitone2, since it's ready-made and relatively easy to use.<br /><br />If you're getting someone else to make the music, make sure they know the capabilities of the music driver before they start. Don't just give them carte blanche to do whatever they want in Famitracker.</div>

