				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">darryl.revok wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How much space is generally used for DPCM samples if a game uses them?</div><br />I think the majority of games use no samples. They eat up a LOT of space for what you get, compared to spending that space on code, etc.<br /><br />When they're in a fixed bank, there's a hard limit of 16k, but since fixed bank space is at a premium it's usually less than 8k dedicated to samples.<br /><br />Some mappers have a bank at C000-DFFF (e.g. MMC3 or FME-7) which makes it really flexible; you have 8k of dedicated space times as many banks as you want to allocate for samples. The most I've ever seen is 4 8k sample banks, used in Gimmick. (32k)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

